            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;This sequence &lt;code&gt;int a = 10, b = 20, c = 30; printf(&quot;a=%d b=%d c=%d\n&quot;, (a = a + b + c), (b = b + b), (c = c + c));&lt;/code&gt; appears to give stable behavior (right-to-left argument evaluation in gcc v7.3.0; result &quot;a=110 b=40 c=60&quot;). Is it because the assignments are considered as &apos;full-statements&apos; and thus introduce a sequence point? Shouldn&apos;t that result in left-to-right argument/statement evaluation? Or, is it just manifestation of undefined behavior?&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/2258526/kavadias&quot; title=&quot;1,017 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;kavadias&lt;/a&gt;
