                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;However if you stick to one compiler, you will find the behavior persistent.&lt;/i&gt; Well, no, not necessarily.  If you, for example, change optimization flags, the compiler may quite easily end up emitting code which makes the undefined behavior behave differently.  Also if you make seemingly-unrelated changes to nearby code.&lt;/span&gt;

